      <agency>The Catholic University of Korea</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>The Catholic University of Korea</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recent study showed that SIBO is common among postgastrectomy patients and It appears to be
      associated with postprandial intestinal symptoms and might aggravate late hypoglycemia. SIBO
      could be a new therapeutic target for managing intestinal symptoms in postgastrectomy
      patients.The purpose of this study is to determine whether antiboitic (metronidazole) is
      effective in patients with postgasrectomy syndrome
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
